r women's team gymnastics at the 2024 Olympics in Paris on July 28, 2024.\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 734, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 711, \"end\": 716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0861257490529645e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Wally Skalij/Los Angeles Times/TNS)  LOS ANGELES - Tom Cruise will take a page out of his \\\"Mission: Impossible\\\" playbook for the Olympic closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.09015217180083e-28, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\"}, {\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_Saints_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9999400244506317, \"rank\": 5.997914650006214e-05, \"text\": \"TNS\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_Saints_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_Saints_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 773, \"end\": 776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Line-of-sight_propagation\", \"score\": 0.9739904636424356, \"rank\": 0.026704097553920166, \"text\": \"LOS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Line-of-sight_propagation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Line-of-sight_propagation\"}, {\"begin\": 787, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 62-year-old actor is reportedly planning an epic stunt that will unfold as Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo hands over the Olympic flag to L.A. Mayor Karen Bass at the Aug. 11 celebration, TMZ first reported.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 1096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 971, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 983, \"end\": 995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 1027, \"end\": 1031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 2.954530377307873e-11, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1038, \"end\": 1048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And he pitched the idea to the International Olympic Committee himself.\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1128, \"end\": 1159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The alleged plan is to have Cruise start by rappelling from the roof of the Stade de France to the stadium's field, Olympic flag in tow.\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(There are also reports that Cruise may use a stunt double for this portion, but nothing is confirmed yet.)\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The broadcast will then cut to a prerecorded segment that shows the Academy Award nominee skydiving down to the Hollywood sign.\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1484, \"end\": 1497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999982640926252, \"rank\": 1.0102272181324693e-06, \"text\": \"Academy Award\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Academy_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 1528, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There, he will pass the flag to athletes, including a cyclist, skateboarder and volleyball player, as they wave it around the host city for the 2028 Games.\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1699, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Hollywood sign sequence was filmed in March, according to TMZ, but given Cruise's penchant for near-lethal stunts, his dive raised little alarm.\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1701, \"end\": 1719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Sign_(film)\", \"score\": 0.9999999997526174, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Sign_(film)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hollywood_Sign_(film)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, sightings of the star speeding around Paris earlier this year were dismissed given \\\"Mission: Impossible 8\\\" was filming in Europe.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0861257490529645e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Representatives for Cruise did not reply immediately Friday to The Times' request for comment.\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2055, \"end\": 2064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"score\": 0.9999996256711502, \"rank\": 3.743288094584854e-07, \"text\": \"The Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 Organizing Committee has declined to discuss ceremony details.\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2091, \"end\": 2101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2763037643177653e-28, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With Paris 2024's artistic director Thomas Jolly at the helm, the closing ceremony - dubbed \\\"Records\\\" - is poised to rival the drama of a Cruise film.\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2171, \"end\": 2181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2763037643177653e-28, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2202, \"end\": 2208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.659442101257795, \"rank\": 0.4900551041525667, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Stade de France will be \\\"transformed into a gigantic concert hall,\\\" the official Olympic website reads, where more than 100 performers, acrobats, dancers and circus artists will \\\"take spectators on a journey through time, both past and future.\\\"\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2566, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a very visual, very choreographic, very acrobatic show with an operatic dimension to give a great visual fresco and say goodbye to athletes from all over the world,\\\" Jolly said.\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2751, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Together, let us make this evening a memorable and conscious celebration, honouring the past and embracing the future.\\\"\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2872, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Expect a major Hollywood production,\\\" a source told Deadline.\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2890, \"end\": 2899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999998358362, \"rank\": 1.6394650776625795e-10, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruise, who in 2004 helped carry the Olympic torch in L.A. as it made its way to Athens, cheered on Team USA during the first week of the Paris Games, attending women's gymnastics and swimming events.\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 3138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2992, \"end\": 2996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 2.954530377307873e-11, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 3019, \"end\": 3025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9268057590284628, \"rank\": 0.0789747368363391, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3038, \"end\": 3046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9574991120365616, \"rank\": 0.03747415227238926, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's awesome,\\\" the \\\"Top Gun: Maverick\\\" star told Reuters.\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3190, \"end\": 3197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.5600960598939974e-11, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Great stories, great athletes.\", \"from\": 3199, \"to\": 3230, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's incredible what they have to do, the sense of accomplishment.\\\"\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3298, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tribune Wire  Your browser is out of date and potentially vulnerable to security risks.We recommend switching to one of the following browsers:\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3443, \"entities\": []}]}"